transport.accessDomain.description:
Access domain of accelerated application for the public users. The HDT API supports multiple domains separated by commas and wildcard to match multiple subdomains. For example:
aaa.domain1.com,*.domain2.com,*.domain3.org.cn

Note:
1. The HDT API supports up to one level of subdomains for "accessDomain" field;
2. "accessDomain" can't be empty; 
3. When "applicationProtocol" is not empty, the combination of "accessDomain" and "applicationProtocol" field must be globally unique;
4. When "applicationProtocol" is empty, the value of "accessDomain" is unique to each customer. Transports belong to the same customer can share "accessDomain".
